verb.description: To make (a vessel, receptacle, etc.) empty; to drain, remove the contents of. Frequently with of: to relieve of certain specified contents; (figurative) to cause to be rid of an attribute, characteristic, etc.
To become empty. In later use with out. rare.
To empty out (the contents of a vessel, receptacle, etc.); to pour out. In later use frequently with out.

origin: Old English (in an earlier sense). Apparently shortened from empty.
